{"lemma":"ضِعْفُ","slug":"ضِعْفُ","root":"ض.ع.ف","root_slug":"ض-ع-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ع-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضِعْف","root":"ضعف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25837","n25842","n25843","n25845"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to weaken","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to weaken, to make weak","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to double","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to geminate (a consonant)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَعُفَ (ḍaʕufa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"weakness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَعُفَ (ḍaʕufa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"weakness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"double"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a multiple, (after numerals) -fold","examples":[{"text":"وَمَثَلُ ٱلَّذِینَ یُنفِقُونَ أَمۡوَ ٰ⁠لَهُمُ ٱبۡتِغَاۤءَ مَرۡضَاتِ ٱللَّهِ وَتَثۡبِیتࣰا مِّنۡ أَنفُسِهِمۡ كَمَثَلِ جَنَّةِۭ بِرَبۡوَةٍ أَصَابَهَا وَابِلࣱ فَـَٔاتَتۡ أُكُلَهَا ضِعۡفَیۡنِ فَإِن لَّمۡ یُصِبۡهَا وَابِلࣱ فَطَلࣱّۗ وَٱللَّهُ بِمَا تَعۡمَلُونَ بَصِیرٌ","english":"And the example of those who donate their wealth, seeking Allah’s pleasure and believing the reward is certain,1 is that of a garden on a fertile hill: when heavy rain falls, it yields up twice its normal produce. If no heavy rain falls, a drizzle is sufficient. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do. — Translated by Dr. Mustafa Khattab, The Clear Quran"},{"text":"إِلاَّ نالَ الآنَ في هٰذهِ الدُّنْيا مائةَ ضِعْفٍ مِنَ البُيوتِ والإِخوَةِ والأَخَواتِ والأُمَّهاتِ والبَنينَ والحُقولِ مع الاِضطِهادات، ونالَ في الآخِرَةِ الحَياةَ الأَبَدِيَّة.","english":"who will not receive one hundred times as much, now in this time: houses, and brothers, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and land, with persecutions, and in the future age eternal life."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25837","headword_ar":"ضَعُفَ","root":"DEf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEafa","text_ar":"ضَعَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1791},{"kind":"text","text":"K,) the latter on the authority of Yoo, (O,) or of Lh, (L,) aor. of each"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuEofN","text_ar":"ضُعْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEofN","text_ar":"ضَعْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * Msb, K) [and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEafN","text_ar":"ضَعَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v. infrà) or this is a simple subst.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEaAfapN","text_ar":"ضَعَافَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEaAfiyapN","text_ar":"ضَعَافِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) all of which are inf. ns. of the former verb, (TA,) or the first, which is of the dial. of Kureysh, is of the former verb, and the second, which is of the dial. of Temeem, is of the latter verb, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, weak, feeble, faint, frail, infirm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsound;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuEofN","text_ar":"ضُعْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEofN","text_ar":"ضَعْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quw~apN","text_ar":"قُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiH~apN","text_ar":"صِحَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and both of them may be used alike, in every relation; or, accord. to the people of El-Basrah, both are so used; so says Az; (TA;) but some say that the former is used in relation to the body, and the latter in relation to the judgment or opinion. (O, Msb, K: but this is omitted in my copy of the TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEufa Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"ضَعُفَ عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lacked strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability, to do"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accomplish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to bear, the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was weak so as to be disabled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incapacitated, from doing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accomplishing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from bearing, the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajaza Eanohu","text_ar":"عَجَزَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ejz","text_ar":"عجز"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajaza Eani A@HotimaAlihi","text_ar":"عَجَزَ عَنِ ا@حْتِمَالِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb in the present art.) ―         -b3-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEofN","text_ar":"ضَعْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEufa","text_ar":"ضَعُفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeded;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAda","text_ar":"زَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) ―         -b2-  And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEafotu Alqawoma","text_ar":"ضَعَفْتُ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K, *) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEofN","text_ar":"ضَعْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O;) [and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEufotu Ealayohimo","text_ar":"ضَعُفْتُ عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zidotu","text_ar":"زِدْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohimo","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I exceeded the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, in number, so that I and my companions had double,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"several-fold, the number that they had."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K. *) ―         -b3-  See also 3."}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","L","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n25842","headword_ar":"ضَعْفٌ","root":"DEf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of 1, like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuEofN","text_ar":"ضُعْفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, *  O, *  Msb, K,) [both, when used as simple substs., signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness, feebleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] but some say that the former is in the judgment or opinion, and the latter in the body; (O, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEafN","text_ar":"ضَعَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, (IAar, K, TA,) and is in the body and also in the judgment or opinion and the intellect. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEofu Alt~aA^oliyfi","text_ar":"ضَعْفُ التَّاْلِيفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness of construction, in language,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a construction of the members of a sentence as is contrary to the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally approved"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rules of syntax;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as when a pronoun is introduced before its noun with respect to the actual order of the words and the order of the sense [in a case in which the pronoun is affixed to the agent in a verbal proposition]; for instance, in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba gulaAmuhu","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ غُلَامُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodFA","text_ar":"زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ His, ” i. e. Zeyd's, “ young man beat Zeyd ”]. (KT.) When the pronoun is affixed to the objective complement, as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAfa rab~ahu Eumaru","text_ar":"خَافَ رَبَّهُ عُمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ 'Omar feared his Lord ”] such introduction of it is common: (I'Ak p. 128:) and it is [universally] allowable when the pronoun is of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Damiyru Al$~aA^oni","text_ar":"ضَمِيرُ الشَّاْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu zayodN qaAy^imN","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ زَيْدٌ قَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Damiyru rub~a","text_ar":"ضَمِيرُ رُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rub~ahu rajulFA laqiytuhu","text_ar":"رُبَّهُ رَجُلًا لَقِيتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Damiyru niEoma","text_ar":"ضَمِيرُ نِعْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEomahu rajulFA zayodN","text_ar":"نِعْمَهُ رَجُلًا زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kull p. 56.) ―         -b3-  [In the CK, a signification belonging to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuEof","text_ar":"ضُعْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEof","text_ar":"ضَعْف"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["IAar","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n25843","headword_ar":"ضُعْفٌ","root":"DEf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEofN","text_ar":"ضَعْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino DuEofK","text_ar":"مِنْ ضُعْفٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur xxx. 53 means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of sperm."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) AA, reciting before the Prophet, said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino DaEofK","text_ar":"مِنْ ضَعْفٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and was told by the latter to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn DuEofK","text_ar":"من ضُعْفٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e.] with damm. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25845","headword_ar":"ضَعَفٌ","root":"DEf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEofN","text_ar":"ضَعْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Garments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of cloth, made double"},{"kind":"text","text":"(↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDaE~FfapN","text_ar":"مُضَعًّفَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}